    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#accessURL> <https://transportdata.be/dataset/b83c0aa0-219c-4eaf-b8f6-ed8ab854554b/resource/0d8aebc7-6a70-475b-9dc6-47275501daca/download/indigo-data-apds-be.json>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#downloadURL> <https://transportdata.be/dataset/b83c0aa0-219c-4eaf-b8f6-ed8ab854554b/resource/0d8aebc7-6a70-475b-9dc6-47275501daca/download/indigo-data-apds-be.json>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/license> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/licence/ODC_BL>;
    <http://data.europa.eu/r5r/availability> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/planned-availability/AVAILABLE>;
    <https://w3id.org/mobilitydcat-ap#applicationLayerProtocol> <https://w3id.org/mobilitydcat-ap/application-layer-protocol/http-https>;
    <https://w3id.org/mobilitydcat-ap#mobilityDataStandard> <https://w3id.org/mobilitydcat-ap/mobility-data-standard/other>;
    <https://w3id.org/mobilitydcat-ap#dataFormatNotes> "L'Alliance for Parking Data Standards (APDS) a développé un standard mondial pour les données de stationnement, basé sur un modèle UML complet.\n    Ce modèle constitue la base des spécifications APDS, qui incluent une vue d’ensemble, un modèle d’information, un modèle de données et des cas d’usage.\n    Pour plus de détails sur la spécification APDS, vous pouvez consulter le dépôt GitHub : https://github.com/parkingdata/spec"@fr, "The Alliance for Parking Data Standards (APDS) has developed a global parking data standard based on a comprehensive UML model.\n    This model serves as the foundation for the APDS Specifications, which include an overview, information model, data model, and use cases.\n    For more details about the APDS specification, please visit the GitHub repository: https://github.com/parkingdata/spec."@en
}
